{"name": "msasim", "metadata": {"name": "msasim", "version": "24.13.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/elyawy/Sailfish-backend", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A fast MSA simulator", "upload_time": 1733326055}, "documentation": ["# Sailfish\n\nSailfish is a performant multiple sequence alignment(MSA) simulator, written in C++ and Python, allowing for quick and easy generation of large simulated datasets. \n\n## Project goals\n\n- Ease of use\n- Speed\n- Modularity\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install msasim\n```\n\n## Example\n\n```python\nfrom msasim import sailfish as sim\nfrom msasim.sailfish import MODEL_CODES, ZipfDistribution\n\nROOT_SEQUENCE_LENGTH = 100\n\nsim_protocol = sim.SimProtocol(\"(A:0.5,B:0.5);\",\n                               deletion_rate=0.01,\n                               insertion_rate=0.01,\n                               deletion_dist=ZipfDistribution(1.08, 50),\n                               insertion_dist=ZipfDistribution(1.08, 50),\n                               seed=50)\nsim_protocol.set_sequence_size(ROOT_SEQUENCE_LENGTH)\n\nsimulation = sim.Simulator(sim_protocol, simulation_type=sim.SIMULATION_TYPE.PROTEIN)\n\nsimulation.set_replacement_model(model=MODEL_CODES.WAG, \n                                 gamma_parameters_alpha=1.0, \n                                 gamma_parameters_catergories=4)\nmsa = simulation()\nmsa.print_msa()\n\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "msasim", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "setup", "documentation": ["Available at setup time due to pyproject.toml"], "functions": [{"name": "setup.print_sources", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sources", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["The main interface is through Pybind11Extension.", "* You can add cxx_std=11/14/17, and then build_ext can be removed.", "* You can set include_pybind11=false to add the include directory yourself,", "say from a submodule.", "Note:", "Sort input source files if you glob sources to ensure bit-for-bit", "reproducible builds (https://github.com/pybind/python_example/pull/53)", "SRC_DIR = Path(\"src\").resolve()"]}], "variables": [{"name": "setup.now", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.ext_modules", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "msasim.sailfish", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "msasim.sailfish.is_newick", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tree", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "msasim.sailfish.MODEL_CODES", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "msasim.sailfish.SIMULATION_TYPE", "bases": ["Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "msasim.sailfish.SIMULATION_TYPE.NOSUBS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "msasim.sailfish.SIMULATION_TYPE.DNA", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "msasim.sailfish.SIMULATION_TYPE.PROTEIN", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "msasim.sailfish.Distribution", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "msasim.sailfish.Distribution.set_dist", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dist", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "msasim.sailfish.Distribution.draw_sample", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "msasim.sailfish.Distribution.set_seed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": nul